HEADWORD: Secondarily
<hw>Sec"ond*a*ri*ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>In a secondary manner or degree.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Secondly; in the second place.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God hath set some in the church, first apostles,
<qex>secondarily</qex> prophets, thirdly teachers.</q> <rj><qau>1 Cor.
xii. 28.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Secondariness</ent>⟦br⟧
